style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What
is seborrheic dermatitis</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Seborrheic dermatitis
is a skin disease manifested by excessive sebum production, rashes in the form
of reddish and yellow spots, and itchy skin.&nbsp;Usually, rashes appear on
areas of the body with a high density of sebaceous glands: on the head among
the hairs, on the face, chest, back, armpits and groin.&nbsp;The disease is not
dangerous.&nbsp;It can affect both adults and infants.&nbsp;Dandruff is a type
of seborrheic dermatitis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
